President Obama convened a meeting with his National Security Council to discuss the reported use of chemical weapons by the Syrian government. The U.S. intelligence community is gathering facts to determine what happened, taking into account witness accounts and the symptoms of those affected. The President received a detailed review of potential options for the U.S. and the international community to respond to the use of chemical weapons. Participants in the meeting included top officials such as the Vice President, Secretary of State, Secretary of Defense, and others.